1
00:00:02,850 --> 00:00:05,430
Episode 12

2
00:00:15,580 --> 00:00:18,390
Let's not get to the point where we can't even be friends.

3
00:00:20,120 --> 00:00:24,730
Let's go back... to the time when we were carefree and could hang out together joyfully.

4
00:00:33,930 --> 00:00:35,710
Choi Won.

5
00:01:00,130 --> 00:01:01,990
Hey Won.

6
00:01:01,990 --> 00:01:03,010
Mm.

7
00:01:03,010 --> 00:01:08,290
I... When you left for your long trip

8
00:01:09,440 --> 00:01:13,160
I felt like I had lost something really precious to me--

9
00:01:13,160 --> 00:01:17,230
I lost my closest friendship

10
00:01:17,230 --> 00:01:19,180
so I was scared.

11
00:01:20,220 --> 00:01:23,370
And I thought that becoming close to you again

12
00:01:24,430 --> 00:01:27,550
would be too selfish of me.

13
00:01:35,380 --> 00:01:38,330
The long time that we have spent together

14
00:01:39,570 --> 00:01:44,540
doesn't have to become a dating relationship or love.

15
00:01:45,720 --> 00:01:49,810
I think that there's still some meaning to it though.

16
00:01:54,970 --> 00:01:57,310
As friends?

17
00:01:57,310 --> 00:02:00,110
Mm. As friends.

18
00:02:04,130 --> 00:02:05,970
Thanks.

19
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:21,870
In the future, I'll support your relationships too.

20
00:02:23,050 --> 00:02:27,770
Supporting sounds good, but seriously, don't criticize or diss my girlfriends.

21
00:02:27,770 --> 00:02:29,870
Okay, I got it.

22
00:02:34,220 --> 00:02:36,050
Oh Ha Na!

23
00:02:43,600 --> 00:02:47,090
Whether it's as a friend or whatever, I can't tolerate

24
00:02:47,090 --> 00:02:49,000
your being close to Oh Ha Na.

25
00:02:49,710 --> 00:02:52,390
- Cha Seo Hoo...
- Let's go

26
00:03:06,040 --> 00:03:10,600
What is it with you two. After you fought with me, you went back to Choi Won again?

27
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:15,820
I already told you. That day, I saw you, after being hurt by me, crying with Choi Won.

28
00:03:15,820 --> 00:03:19,220
Seo Hoo. Don't you think you should at least ask first?

29
00:03:19,220 --> 00:03:22,230
Don't you think you should ask, "Why? What happened? How did you end up hanging out with Choi Won?"

30
00:03:22,230 --> 00:03:26,100
Are you really going to get angry like this just because we were hanging out?

31
00:03:26,100 --> 00:03:29,110
Choi Won is my friend. Both that day and today.

32
00:03:29,110 --> 00:03:31,210
Choi Won has always been by my side as a friend.

33
00:03:31,210 --> 00:03:32,560
You expect me to believe that?

34
00:03:32,560 --> 00:03:33,990
Why can't you believe it?

35
00:03:33,990 --> 00:03:36,680
Then three years ago why did you just leave?

36
00:03:36,680 --> 00:03:40,770
Why didn't you let out your anger like this then? Why did you just disappear?

37
00:03:46,060 --> 00:03:48,120
Despite what everyone said,

38
00:03:48,970 --> 00:03:51,640
even though my family didn't approve.

39
00:03:52,380 --> 00:03:56,990
I even chose you over my longest friendship,

40
00:03:58,400 --> 00:04:01,730
because the memories of being hurt by you

41
00:04:03,130 --> 00:04:06,450
weren't important at all to me.

42
00:04:08,710 --> 00:04:11,520
Because you

43
00:04:11,520 --> 00:04:14,470
are not someone that I can push away.

44
00:04:22,010 --> 00:04:25,860
♬ Was it always warm ♬

45
00:04:25,860 --> 00:04:28,800
Cha Seo Hoo, you seriously....

46
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:34,740
♬ With you as the only one for me ♬

47
00:04:35,530 --> 00:04:39,180
I'm sorry.
♬ Is it okay to laugh about it ♬

48
00:04:39,180 --> 00:04:42,520
♬ The hard days past ♬

49
00:04:42,520 --> 00:04:48,450
♬ Because you were always there ♬

50
00:04:48,450 --> 00:04:55,480
♬ Even my heart didn't know how I felt ♬

51
00:04:55,480 --> 00:05:02,320
♬ Perhaps because you were always beside me ♬

52
00:05:02,320 --> 00:05:06,330
♬ From when it was ♬
♬ Or how it started ♬

53
00:05:06,330 --> 00:05:10,020
♬ Or how it started ♬

54
00:05:10,020 --> 00:05:18,980
♬ Neither you nor I were aware ♬

55
00:05:20,520 --> 00:05:23,870
Team Leader Oh Ha Na, I've already reported everything about the ChaAndy deal,

56
00:05:23,870 --> 00:05:25,770
and when we're going to begin selling the merchandise.

57
00:05:25,770 --> 00:05:28,580
Please tell her some of the details of the event.

58
00:05:28,580 --> 00:05:31,480
-Yes.
- Okay then.

59
00:05:36,300 --> 00:05:38,060
Next week, we are looking to

60
00:05:38,060 --> 00:05:42,000
launch the collaboration project from the department store.

61
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:43,540
The fundraising event is scheduled for next month--

62
00:05:43,540 --> 00:05:47,930
The event may be cancelled because of the world tour.

63
00:05:47,930 --> 00:05:51,090
From today, please leave this project.

64
00:05:52,020 --> 00:05:53,530
Excuse me?

65
00:05:55,870 --> 00:05:58,780
I dislike having to repeat myself.

66
00:05:59,920 --> 00:06:03,660
Is this something you've discussed with Mr. Cha?

67
00:06:08,540 --> 00:06:11,790
I am the one who represents the company.

68
00:06:11,790 --> 00:06:16,750
That may be, but shouldn't the company take care of the artist's reputation?

69
00:06:16,750 --> 00:06:20,790
Part of this project includes doing personal interviews.

70
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:26,000
- If all these things are suddenly cancelled, what would happen to Mr. Cha's image?
- What are you saying?

71
00:06:26,010 --> 00:06:28,750
Will showing Mr. Cha as the kind of person who can't keep small promises

72
00:06:28,750 --> 00:06:32,090
because a world tour really be the best?

73
00:06:32,090 --> 00:06:35,340
Are you criticizing me right now?

74
00:06:35,340 --> 00:06:39,530
I'm not criticizing you. I simply don't understand.

75
00:06:41,590 --> 00:06:44,120
In this world,

76
00:06:44,990 --> 00:06:47,170
there are plenty of things that you won't understand.

77
00:06:49,440 --> 00:06:53,040
Well, in the world that I am living in, there are no such exceptions allowed.

78
00:06:53,040 --> 00:06:55,170
Please reconsider.

79
00:07:18,500 --> 00:07:20,360
Yeah, Seo Hoo?

80
00:07:20,360 --> 00:07:25,000
I understand what you're saying. I'm not going to do the world tour.

81
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:27,460
It's merely CEO Min's opinion.

82
00:07:27,460 --> 00:07:32,010
For the last three years, I've worked hard enough. I came here to take a break.

83
00:07:33,850 --> 00:07:37,310
Continue with the charity concert.

84
00:07:45,720 --> 00:07:52,750
Timing and Subtitles brought to you by The Timeless Lovers @ Viki

85
00:08:02,810 --> 00:08:07,140
Among our first-class passengers, we have a patient in the last stage of cancer.

86
00:08:07,140 --> 00:08:09,820
The guardian and the doctor will accompany the patient

87
00:08:09,820 --> 00:08:13,550
but in case the passenger is in need of special care,

88
00:08:13,550 --> 00:08:15,400
please be prepared.

89
00:08:15,400 --> 00:08:16,970
Yes.

90
00:08:34,310 --> 00:08:35,970
Excuse me, professor.

91
00:08:41,030 --> 00:08:43,080
Do you remember me?

92
00:08:43,080 --> 00:08:47,900
It's Choi Won, from Dongbang High School. I was in Room 1 in 11th grade, number 43.

93
00:08:52,530 --> 00:08:54,570
Ah! Choi Won!

94
00:09:11,490 --> 00:09:13,310
What--

95
00:09:14,400 --> 00:09:15,580
Are you being bullied or something?

96
00:09:15,580 --> 00:09:20,690
It's lunchtime. Why are you just staring out the window instead of eating?

97
00:09:25,530 --> 00:09:29,180
You like her, don't you?

98
00:09:30,930 --> 00:09:32,620
N-No. No I don't.

99
00:09:32,620 --> 00:09:34,080
What do you mean, no.

100
00:09:34,080 --> 00:09:35,960
I don't have anyone to eat with - would you like to eat together?

101
00:09:35,960 --> 00:09:37,930
No, thank you.

102
00:09:37,930 --> 00:09:40,280
I would have indigestion if I ate with my teacher.

103
00:09:41,770 --> 00:09:45,440
Your script was great.

104
00:09:45,440 --> 00:09:50,020
I'm curious - who is the main character's friend, who's the girl the main character's friend likes,

105
00:09:50,020 --> 00:09:53,930
and who does the girl like?

106
00:09:53,930 --> 00:09:57,190
I think I might know whom they are, but I'm not sure,

107
00:09:57,190 --> 00:10:02,080
just from my experience from teaching for so long.

108
00:10:03,060 --> 00:10:05,800
Don't not eat just because your mother isn't around.

109
00:10:05,800 --> 00:10:07,580
If you're hungry, then let me know.

110
00:10:07,580 --> 00:10:11,370
You, such a talented writer, deserve such a treat.

111
00:10:12,280 --> 00:10:13,240
Thank you.

112
00:10:13,240 --> 00:10:18,290
But don't become a writer. You'll be hungry.

113
00:10:22,030 --> 00:10:26,170
I remember.  Are you still writing?

114
00:10:26,170 --> 00:10:31,430
Seeing you here, I guess you're not a writer, right?

115
00:10:31,430 --> 00:10:34,020
Yes. It seems you do remember.

116
00:10:34,020 --> 00:10:36,330
I should have been better about keeping in touch. I'm sorry.

117
00:10:36,330 --> 00:10:38,260
What do you mean"sorry", there's nothing to be sorry about.

118
00:10:38,260 --> 00:10:41,190
I'm just glad we've been able to meet.

119
00:10:42,880 --> 00:10:44,590
Is there anything I can get you?

120
00:10:45,360 --> 00:10:50,010
This trip also marks our 35th anniversary.

121
00:10:51,300 --> 00:10:53,780
Ah okay.

122
00:10:54,820 --> 00:10:56,750
Just a moment, please.

123
00:11:07,790 --> 00:11:09,420
What are you doing, Sunbaenim?

124
00:11:09,420 --> 00:11:13,970
Oh... a special gift.

125
00:11:19,380 --> 00:11:21,690
What is this, Won?

126
00:11:21,690 --> 00:11:25,600
Teacher, this is my small gift, hoping your journey will be a pleasurable one.

127
00:11:25,600 --> 00:11:29,130
Oh my... It's really pretty!

128
00:11:29,130 --> 00:11:32,600
Thanks to you it became a perfect journey.

129
00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:37,190
I hope I can serve you on your next journey.

130
00:11:39,270 --> 00:11:42,450
The script you've written...

131
00:11:42,450 --> 00:11:45,150
I have it at home, take it with you.

132
00:11:45,150 --> 00:11:47,610
You are still keeping that?

133
00:11:47,610 --> 00:11:49,550
Yeah, I will stop by at your house soon.

134
00:11:49,550 --> 00:11:51,730
Yes, sure.

135
00:11:52,850 --> 00:11:59,610
Won, live your moments without regret,

136
00:11:59,610 --> 00:12:03,340
I really want you to do that.

137
00:12:07,820 --> 00:12:10,770
Yes, Teacher.

138
00:12:19,820 --> 00:12:23,150
As expected Sunbaenim Choi is extraordinary.

139
00:12:23,150 --> 00:12:27,130
Anybody can do that kind of act.

140
00:12:27,130 --> 00:12:29,510
You like cake too, So Eun?

141
00:12:29,510 --> 00:12:31,610
I'm okay.

142
00:12:33,260 --> 00:12:37,120
He alway does that sort of thing to stand out.

143
00:12:37,120 --> 00:12:39,820
It is not standing out but having sense.

144
00:12:39,820 --> 00:12:41,620
Yes, yes.

145
00:12:41,620 --> 00:12:44,890
Did I say anything? Did I?

146
00:12:53,270 --> 00:12:55,620
Is this part of the 1+1 deal too?

147
00:12:55,620 --> 00:12:57,810
- Wow!
- Do you like them?

148
00:13:12,610 --> 00:13:14,820
Is there anything I can help you with?

149
00:13:21,210 --> 00:13:23,030
Wait.

150
00:13:23,030 --> 00:13:26,490
Would you please bring me a small table and a chair?

151
00:13:26,490 --> 00:13:28,330
Yes.

152
00:13:29,300 --> 00:13:32,790
Why? What did you say?

153
00:13:32,790 --> 00:13:37,630
♫ From when was my feeling love?  ♫

154
00:13:37,630 --> 00:13:42,380
♫ Are you shining eyes looking at me love?  ♫

155
00:13:42,380 --> 00:13:47,510
♫ Shall I try to tell you once now?  ♫

156
00:13:47,510 --> 00:13:53,820
♫ Shall we try to start our love? Why are we like this? ♫

157
00:13:53,820 --> 00:14:01,520
♫ Someone teach me. I still don't really know what love is ♫

158
00:14:01,520 --> 00:14:06,190
♫ Where? How? Why did it come now?   ♫

159
00:14:06,190 --> 00:14:08,010
We sold a lot.

160
00:14:08,010 --> 00:14:09,790
The effect of Cha Seo Hoo's autograph is pretty great.

161
00:14:09,790 --> 00:14:13,720
The agreed percentage of shoe sales will be donated to the needy, right?

162
00:14:13,720 --> 00:14:15,930
- Yes.
- What a great idea.

163
00:14:15,930 --> 00:14:20,090
When we donate the shoes, there will be a photo session and interviews again.

164
00:14:20,090 --> 00:14:23,640
I'll let you handle all of it and I will just follow you.

165
00:14:23,640 --> 00:14:25,800
Thank you.

166
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:44,980
Oh, this is so refreshing.

167
00:14:44,980 --> 00:14:47,710
Now stop it and just leave.

168
00:14:47,710 --> 00:14:49,240
I have something to tell you.

169
00:14:49,240 --> 00:14:52,020
Tell me here. It is nice and comfortable.

170
00:14:52,020 --> 00:14:54,950
It's not the kind of talk to have in this sort of atmosphere.

171
00:14:54,950 --> 00:14:57,120
We still have a lot of time before we get our money's worth.

172
00:14:57,120 --> 00:14:59,030
It's only been two hours.

173
00:14:59,030 --> 00:15:01,740
Am I that comfortable to you, Jong Hoon?

174
00:15:01,740 --> 00:15:03,750
We only met twice.

175
00:15:03,750 --> 00:15:06,380
The first meeting was at the potato stew restaurant, and today at the sauna.

176
00:15:06,380 --> 00:15:09,880
Isn't this too relaxing?

177
00:15:09,880 --> 00:15:12,930
Let's stop seeing each other. Our tastes are too different.

178
00:15:12,930 --> 00:15:16,880
If they don't fit, then we match them as we go.

179
00:15:16,880 --> 00:15:19,350
Next time let's go wherever you want.

180
00:15:19,350 --> 00:15:22,060
Excuse me did you even hear what is just said?

181
00:15:22,060 --> 00:15:24,400
I am saying to stop meeting each other!

182
00:15:24,400 --> 00:15:27,620
Why am I saying this at a sauna...

183
00:15:27,620 --> 00:15:31,050
First eat and then let's think about it.

184
00:15:33,330 --> 00:15:37,290
Next time, don't wear makeup.

185
00:15:37,290 --> 00:15:40,330
You are prettier without the makeup, Mi Hyang.

186
00:15:41,990 --> 00:15:45,380
I don't like roasted eggs!

187
00:15:48,550 --> 00:15:50,800
Mi Hyang!

188
00:15:53,920 --> 00:15:55,200
Mi Hyang!

189
00:15:55,200 --> 00:15:58,090
To where are you going to follow me?

190
00:15:58,090 --> 00:16:00,210
Let's see each other here later.

191
00:16:00,210 --> 00:16:02,390
Forget it. Don't contact me.

192
00:16:02,390 --> 00:16:04,540
I will call you.

193
00:16:11,570 --> 00:16:13,460
Hey!

194
00:16:13,460 --> 00:16:16,490
Hey! This...

195
00:16:16,490 --> 00:16:18,810
What, what is all this?

196
00:16:18,810 --> 00:16:22,670
I am going to cook for people in this family.

197
00:16:22,670 --> 00:16:27,170
Why do you cook? No, no! Don't!

198
00:16:27,170 --> 00:16:33,520
No it's just... you don't have to do it already.

199
00:16:33,520 --> 00:16:39,090
I felt bad for causing my parents heartache.

200
00:16:42,330 --> 00:16:47,380
Ha Na, can't you just... let Mom do it?

201
00:16:47,380 --> 00:16:54,820
If you wash up and wait a bit you will eat well, isn't it better?

202
00:16:56,810 --> 00:17:00,870
I already memorized the recipe.

203
00:17:00,870 --> 00:17:04,360
Cooking is not done by memorization...

204
00:17:04,360 --> 00:17:08,580
The taste is created with the fingertips...

205
00:17:10,130 --> 00:17:11,850
Hyung!

206
00:17:11,850 --> 00:17:14,020
What's going on? You are scary.

207
00:17:14,020 --> 00:17:18,060
Noona is cooking now. You don't want to eat it and neither do I.

208
00:17:18,060 --> 00:17:20,070
So let's buy and eat it.

209
00:17:20,070 --> 00:17:22,060
Uh, hey.

210
00:17:22,060 --> 00:17:24,730
What's wrong? I want to eat. I'm hungry.

211
00:17:24,730 --> 00:17:29,220
Do you think that what Noona will cook will be edible? Do you really think so?

212
00:17:29,220 --> 00:17:31,870
Your Noona made me some porridge when I was sick the other day, and

213
00:17:31,870 --> 00:17:34,040
that was really good.

214
00:17:34,040 --> 00:17:38,640
Indeed, you are probably the only one who will defend my noona.

215
00:17:38,640 --> 00:17:40,940
Actually...

216
00:17:41,940 --> 00:17:45,750
I have a secret I can't tell to my parents.

217
00:17:45,750 --> 00:17:47,870
What is that? ...Again?

218
00:17:47,870 --> 00:17:51,900
The president of that rabbit jerk's contracting company is in Korea...

219
00:17:51,900 --> 00:17:57,050
They were saying there were scandals with the chaebol woman or whatever.

220
00:17:58,310 --> 00:18:00,270
Really?

221
00:18:06,570 --> 00:18:11,570
Just sharing my secret information with Hyung is making me feel lighter.

222
00:18:11,570 --> 00:18:14,980
This punk...

223
00:18:31,420 --> 00:18:35,160
Who will be pleased with this? This small thing? It's just one bite.

224
00:18:35,160 --> 00:18:38,260
Let's eat if first and eat some rice again. Won't that work?

225
00:18:38,260 --> 00:18:41,330
High class cuisine depends on taste rather than quantity.

226
00:18:41,330 --> 00:18:43,660
Eat!

227
00:18:50,430 --> 00:18:53,510
Uh, this is unexpectedly good.

228
00:18:53,510 --> 00:18:55,890
- Really?
- It's okay.

229
00:18:55,890 --> 00:18:58,660
My daughter is a good cook. Is a refill allowed?

230
00:18:58,660 --> 00:19:01,860
Of course, Dad!

231
00:19:01,860 --> 00:19:05,570
But you two... I cooked but what's up with you?

232
00:19:05,570 --> 00:19:07,350
How much were you expecting from me?

233
00:19:07,350 --> 00:19:09,520
Every time Noona cooks I am disappointed.

234
00:19:09,520 --> 00:19:11,930
For sure you will tell me to cleanup, right, Mom?

235
00:19:11,930 --> 00:19:16,360
Isn't that given? You just play and eat and don't do anything around the house--

236
00:19:16,360 --> 00:19:18,140
Okay, I got it.

237
00:19:18,140 --> 00:19:21,570
Wash dishes, cleaning, trash, I do it all.

238
00:19:21,570 --> 00:19:25,150
While you are at it, clean the bathroom and my room.

239
00:19:25,150 --> 00:19:27,790
If I work this much, will this be enough?

240
00:19:27,790 --> 00:19:30,490
Should I give you more?

241
00:19:31,580 --> 00:19:35,380
Oh so nice!

242
00:19:35,380 --> 00:19:37,700
Eat.

243
00:19:39,580 --> 00:19:43,270
- It's good!
- Sure, I told you so!

244
00:19:59,100 --> 00:20:01,800
This is to notify you that Teacher Park Young Soo died on July 30th, 7:30 a.m.

245
00:20:01,800 --> 00:20:04,910
Funeral at the Hangang Hospital Funeral Hall August 1, 6 pm. Burial ...

246
00:20:43,310 --> 00:20:45,770
Thanks for coming.

247
00:21:17,540 --> 00:21:19,790
Are you graduates of Dongbang High?

248
00:21:19,790 --> 00:21:21,580
Yes.

249
00:21:21,580 --> 00:21:23,740
Would you please write down your name and the year you graduated?

250
00:21:33,140 --> 00:21:37,200
Ah, I remember you. You are the flight attendant, right?

251
00:21:37,200 --> 00:21:39,050
Yes. How did you...

252
00:21:39,050 --> 00:21:43,930
My father was really happy meeting one of his pupils during his recent trip.

253
00:21:46,110 --> 00:21:50,030
If your time permits, may I invite you to "Conversation with Sunbae"?

254
00:21:50,030 --> 00:21:53,110
I am also teaching kids in school.

255
00:21:53,820 --> 00:21:57,770
Yes, sure. Call me when you feel like it.

256
00:22:00,760 --> 00:22:03,990
- Yeah.
- Eat a lot and continue with your conversation.

257
00:22:03,990 --> 00:22:07,490
It's good to see you after so long but this occasion is a bit...

258
00:22:07,490 --> 00:22:11,800
It'd been a really long time since I had seen our professor too. I really regret it now.

259
00:22:11,800 --> 00:22:15,320
- Won, you said you met him on the plane?
- Yes.

260
00:22:15,320 --> 00:22:19,320
He was on a trip with his wife for their 35th anniversary.

261
00:22:20,050 --> 00:22:23,050
- How hard must it have been.
- Aigoo...

262
00:22:23,640 --> 00:22:28,580
Being over 30 years of age, there are too many weddings or funerals to attend.

263
00:22:28,580 --> 00:22:35,740
I'm grateful though, that at least, out of the people from high school, the only ones I was close to were Dae Yoon and the professor.

264
00:22:35,740 --> 00:22:38,190
Ah, Dae Yoon.

265
00:22:38,190 --> 00:22:40,880
That's right. I remember him.

266
00:22:40,880 --> 00:22:43,560
Oh, you were close with him, right?

267
00:22:43,560 --> 00:22:45,380
Yeah.

268
00:22:47,000 --> 00:22:51,370
They said that out of the things the professor left behind, he had some things to give to his students and that we should go to get them.

269
00:22:51,370 --> 00:22:53,770
Hey, Ha Na, do you remember Dae Yoon?

270
00:22:53,770 --> 00:22:57,880
Dae Yoon? Well, a bit.

271
00:22:57,880 --> 00:23:02,230
A bit? Psh. He really liked you, you know?

272
00:23:02,760 --> 00:23:05,940
Really? I didn't really know.

273
00:23:05,940 --> 00:23:09,030
When I was in high school, I was pretty popular, huh.

274
00:23:10,540 --> 00:23:14,250
The teacher's family was a little sad because there weren't that many graduates

275
00:23:14,250 --> 00:23:18,080
who kept in touch with him.

276
00:23:18,080 --> 00:23:20,020
What can you do? Everybody is busy making a living after graduation.

277
00:23:20,020 --> 00:23:24,580
It is hard enough to take care your own family and friends, let alone the teacher.

278
00:23:27,060 --> 00:23:29,080
Let's go now.

279
00:23:37,750 --> 00:23:39,850
Kang Na Yeong

280
00:23:45,190 --> 00:23:47,390
What about me?

281
00:23:47,390 --> 00:23:50,600
That's because you weren't involved in activities.

282
00:23:50,600 --> 00:23:53,470
You were too busy dating Jeong Mi.

283
00:23:53,470 --> 00:23:56,800
Chang Soo, look! There you are.

284
00:23:58,040 --> 00:24:02,320
The teacher must have already known that you two would get married.

285
00:24:14,800 --> 00:24:16,860
Hey Won, let me see yours too.

286
00:24:19,220 --> 00:24:21,180
Sure.

287
00:24:28,700 --> 00:24:31,960
What are you looking at in this picture, so seriously?

288
00:24:36,850 --> 00:24:40,960
That's right, your dream was to be a movie director, right?

289
00:24:42,830 --> 00:24:44,860
Didn't you say you have an appointment?

290
00:24:46,160 --> 00:24:48,580
Yes, you?

291
00:24:49,560 --> 00:24:52,500
Me too.  There's somewhere I have to go.

292
00:25:02,450 --> 00:25:04,700
Your sudden appearance

293
00:25:05,370 --> 00:25:07,690
isn't welcome.

294
00:25:17,910 --> 00:25:20,940
This is the exact same as three years ago.

295
00:25:20,940 --> 00:25:23,840
The same women, the same situation.

296
00:25:23,840 --> 00:25:28,490
Even so, I suppose the fact that I came after you this time is different.

297
00:25:29,250 --> 00:25:32,660
Is Cha Seo Hoo's popularity different?

298
00:25:32,660 --> 00:25:36,810
I want to wrap up the contract with you on good terms.

299
00:25:38,940 --> 00:25:44,070
You got in bed with the Top Classic In order to get power, but after you got the power...

300
00:25:44,070 --> 00:25:45,790
I...

301
00:25:45,790 --> 00:25:48,830
am an obstacle to you now?

302
00:25:51,530 --> 00:25:56,220
I made the agreement with you for Oh Ha Na.

303
00:25:56,820 --> 00:25:58,870
Then?

304
00:25:58,870 --> 00:26:01,850
Then, if I were to get rid of Oh Ha Na,

305
00:26:01,850 --> 00:26:05,870
are you going to keep the agreement with me?

306
00:26:05,870 --> 00:26:07,140
What are you saying?

307
00:26:07,140 --> 00:26:12,660
Three years ago, the real reason why you weren't able to go to the engagement party,

308
00:26:14,650 --> 00:26:17,410
how would it be if I told her?

309
00:26:21,530 --> 00:26:23,550
Will you please leave?

310
00:26:23,550 --> 00:26:26,030
This is my personal space.

311
00:26:37,000 --> 00:26:39,180
Oh Ha Na.

312
00:26:41,360 --> 00:26:43,630
Why her?

313
00:26:47,250 --> 00:26:48,970
Of course...

314
00:26:49,840 --> 00:26:53,610
I did like your immature side...

315
00:26:55,840 --> 00:27:03,170
Timing and Subtitles brought to you by The Timeless Lovers @ Viki

316
00:27:08,670 --> 00:27:11,910
Yes, Seo Hoo, I'm almost there.

317
00:27:31,430 --> 00:27:33,470
I'm glad that you came.

318
00:27:33,470 --> 00:27:36,170
What's going on?

319
00:27:43,190 --> 00:27:45,590
I wasn't feeling good.

320
00:27:45,590 --> 00:27:48,370
But because of you, my mood is lifted.

321
00:27:50,630 --> 00:27:52,620
What's going on?

322
00:27:53,490 --> 00:27:55,650
Nothing.

323
00:27:57,740 --> 00:27:59,630
Let's go in.

324
00:28:52,680 --> 00:28:54,940
Should I get you something to drink?

325
00:28:58,810 --> 00:29:05,080
Actually, no. You've been practicing for over two hours. Let's go out and get something yummy.

326
00:29:05,080 --> 00:29:08,590
No.  I don't want to go out.

327
00:29:08,590 --> 00:29:10,900
I just want to stay here.

328
00:29:26,580 --> 00:29:29,090
Did something happen today?

329
00:29:30,830 --> 00:29:34,560
No.  I'm just tired.

330
00:29:34,560 --> 00:29:38,010
Seo Hoo, do you want to just be alone today?

331
00:29:43,620 --> 00:29:47,830
You didn't even ask how my teacher's funeral went today...

332
00:29:47,830 --> 00:29:50,030
Did it go well?

333
00:29:51,960 --> 00:29:53,780
Yes.

334
00:30:24,790 --> 00:30:31,400
Eun Dae Yoon.

335
00:30:44,230 --> 00:30:45,890
Play ball.

336
00:30:46,480 --> 00:30:50,510
Have you given my letter to Oh Ha Na yet?
- Just do it yourself!

337
00:30:50,510 --> 00:30:54,310
I am going to try just ten times. You by any chance...

338
00:30:54,310 --> 00:30:56,320
Do you like Oh Ha Na?

339
00:30:56,960 --> 00:30:59,290
Are you crazy?

340
00:31:02,430 --> 00:31:04,550
I'm trusting you.

341
00:31:07,380 --> 00:31:10,810
I left it in your bag.
Hey!

342
00:31:46,640 --> 00:31:48,450
Then,

343
00:31:49,500 --> 00:31:52,650
for failing to deliver your letter

344
00:31:52,650 --> 00:31:55,690
I won't be sorry anymore.

345
00:31:55,690 --> 00:31:57,450
Now...

346
00:31:58,040 --> 00:32:01,320
I've realized the true feelings in my heart.

347
00:32:05,060 --> 00:32:08,060
I couldn't confess properly.

348
00:32:08,060 --> 00:32:11,960
Immature and young...

349
00:32:11,960 --> 00:32:16,040
I am leaving my old self from then here.

350
00:32:20,640 --> 00:32:22,650
Stay well.

351
00:32:52,820 --> 00:32:56,080
Looking at you looking so tired from the back is such an unpleasant sight, Oh Ha Na.

352
00:32:56,080 --> 00:32:58,580
Choi Won..

353
00:32:58,580 --> 00:33:02,010
Is the fact that I lost my strength noticeable?

354
00:33:02,010 --> 00:33:07,030
Yup! You aren't standing up straight, instead you are listing over 30 degrees.

355
00:33:07,920 --> 00:33:11,780
I will give you your observational ability.

356
00:33:11,780 --> 00:33:14,660
It's good that you're walking in front of me.

357
00:33:14,660 --> 00:33:15,630
Why?

358
00:33:15,630 --> 00:33:20,210
Because I don't have to show you my tired and lifeless expression.

359
00:33:20,210 --> 00:33:22,980
It's just one of those days that I don't have energy.

360
00:33:22,980 --> 00:33:26,640
There was the teacher's funeral, and work...

361
00:33:26,640 --> 00:33:29,260
Yeah, you're right.

362
00:33:29,260 --> 00:33:31,660
I like having you walk behind me better too.

363
00:33:31,660 --> 00:33:34,320
Yeah, it's nice to not have to see my expression, right?

364
00:33:34,320 --> 00:33:37,520
Yeah, you're right. Were you able to figure everything out with Cha Seo Hoo?

365
00:33:37,520 --> 00:33:39,440
Mm. Yeah.

366
00:33:39,440 --> 00:33:42,080
That's good. I worried for nothing then.

367
00:33:42,080 --> 00:33:45,970
Seo Hoo has been really busy lately.

368
00:33:45,970 --> 00:33:49,550
So that's why you're coming home early.

369
00:33:49,550 --> 00:33:53,580
Hey, show me that script you wrote.

370
00:33:53,580 --> 00:33:59,780
Hey! What're you doing, instead of walking?

371
00:34:02,400 --> 00:34:03,580
There isn't really anything to see.

372
00:34:03,580 --> 00:34:09,170
If there isn't anything to see, just show me then. If you don't show me, I'm only going to get more curious.

373
00:34:09,170 --> 00:34:15,390
The more you hide the more valuable your life becomes.

374
00:34:15,390 --> 00:34:17,840
Fine. If you don't want to show me, then don't.

375
00:34:17,840 --> 00:34:19,680
I'll show you.

376
00:34:19,680 --> 00:34:22,940
But, you can't say that, because it's good, that you want to make a movie out of it or

377
00:34:22,940 --> 00:34:25,100
use it as a story for marketing.

378
00:34:25,100 --> 00:34:29,370
I will analyze it critically, so you just wait.

379
00:34:37,710 --> 00:34:39,940
[Year 2001 Graduate
Oh Ha Na]

380
00:34:54,060 --> 00:34:57,330
Where could I have been looking?

381
00:34:57,330 --> 00:35:02,020
When did the teacher take these kinds of pictures?

382
00:35:06,520 --> 00:35:09,580
$50, $50...$5--

383
00:35:09,580 --> 00:35:14,680
How come there are so many congratulatory events? I need at least $200 next month.

384
00:35:14,680 --> 00:35:17,360
Just try getting married...

385
00:35:17,360 --> 00:35:20,240
$200 is nothing.  In some months,

386
00:35:20,240 --> 00:35:22,480
the whole month of living expense budget will be gone.

387
00:35:22,480 --> 00:35:25,880
I have nothing to spend money on since my relationship ended.

388
00:35:25,880 --> 00:35:30,230
- Is it a good thing?
- Think of it in whichever way is better for your mental health.

389
00:35:32,180 --> 00:35:34,420
There's not much time left for you, either, Choi Won.

390
00:35:34,420 --> 00:35:36,980
- Sunbae! It's time for you to take us out.
- How about a night club?

391
00:35:36,980 --> 00:35:40,320
Let's sweat it out for a change, and meet girls too.

392
00:35:40,320 --> 00:35:43,540
How long has it been since your relationship ended that you're already thinking of other things?

393
00:35:43,540 --> 00:35:47,640
Don't you know anything? You forget your previous love with another love.

394
00:35:47,640 --> 00:35:52,010
At any rate, whether it is a club or a hut I am in,

395
00:35:52,010 --> 00:35:55,770
just pick a specific day.

396
00:35:55,770 --> 00:35:59,720
I have to get my wife's permission in advance.

397
00:35:59,720 --> 00:36:02,300
- Go ahead and get her permission--
- Fine I will treat you guys.

398
00:36:02,300 --> 00:36:04,840
Just pick whatever day you like.

399
00:36:04,840 --> 00:36:07,460
Oh yeah!!

400
00:36:07,460 --> 00:36:09,420
For you.

401
00:36:11,180 --> 00:36:12,700
Thanks.

402
00:36:15,320 --> 00:36:18,300
Ice coffee.

403
00:36:18,300 --> 00:36:22,460
Americano - I like it, I like it.

404
00:36:27,280 --> 00:36:28,870
What was that?

405
00:36:31,930 --> 00:36:36,070
I was the one who bought it. What's he doing?

406
00:36:52,150 --> 00:36:55,400
Why did you contact me again?

407
00:36:56,840 --> 00:37:01,040
- I said I didn't want to meet anymore.
- You came out anyway, and here you are.

408
00:37:04,980 --> 00:37:08,480
I see you've dressed like a pianist today.

409
00:37:08,480 --> 00:37:10,940
I have someone I need to impress.

410
00:37:13,340 --> 00:37:14,980
Here!

411
00:37:30,220 --> 00:37:34,000
Do you two know each other?

412
00:37:50,740 --> 00:37:53,590
Just a moment, please.

413
00:38:08,240 --> 00:38:12,520
- We're even meeting in a place like this.
-You're uncomfortable that I'm here, right?

414
00:38:12,520 --> 00:38:14,810
Why would I, because of Won?

415
00:38:16,420 --> 00:38:21,800
Don't you think I'd notice my brother's feelings, being his Noona?

416
00:38:23,100 --> 00:38:24,730
I'm sorry, Unni.

417
00:38:24,730 --> 00:38:27,710
There's nothing to be sorry about.

418
00:38:27,710 --> 00:38:32,170
I understand Won's feelings, but I understand yours too.

419
00:38:32,170 --> 00:38:35,080
I kept thinking of Won,

420
00:38:35,080 --> 00:38:38,500
and had originally planned to give up on meeting with Seo Eun,

421
00:38:38,500 --> 00:38:42,820
but in one phone call, all my thoughts seemed to change.

422
00:38:43,940 --> 00:38:46,680
I felt like I couldn't even do what I wanted to do.

423
00:38:48,560 --> 00:38:51,180
But, it's so nice.

424
00:38:52,680 --> 00:38:54,760
Thank you, Unni.

425
00:39:03,360 --> 00:39:10,990
Timing and Subtitles brought to you by The Timeless Lovers @ Viki

426
00:39:24,480 --> 00:39:26,030
What're you doing?

427
00:39:27,240 --> 00:39:30,380
What's upset you so much that you're treating the poor arcade game like that?

428
00:39:30,380 --> 00:39:32,160
Is it that obvious that I'm upset?

429
00:39:32,160 --> 00:39:35,900
Are you kidding? Your arm was going back this far.

430
00:39:35,900 --> 00:39:39,560
- I bet if someone were hit by that they would get knocked out.
- You want to get hit instead?

431
00:39:39,560 --> 00:39:41,000
Nope.

432
00:39:49,780 --> 00:39:55,600
It seems like everything is going well, but I still feel some anxiety.

433
00:39:56,960 --> 00:39:58,960
I think the heat is affecting me.

434
00:39:59,880 --> 00:40:03,810
Perhaps it is because you have only been too comfortable and good things are happening to you?

435
00:40:03,810 --> 00:40:08,500
Sometimes you are more comfortable with unbelievable situations and absurd matters.

436
00:40:08,500 --> 00:40:13,860
You are right. Like when you are extremely busy and getting pecked from the top and from the bottom and having a rough time,

437
00:40:13,860 --> 00:40:18,160
your body is totally exhausted but your heart feels light and good.

438
00:40:21,520 --> 00:40:24,240
After seeing the teacher's funeral,

439
00:40:26,360 --> 00:40:29,420
it makes me think of when my dad passed away.

440
00:40:34,040 --> 00:40:36,480
He had been bedridden for a long time.

441
00:40:36,480 --> 00:40:39,400
About a day before he passed away...

442
00:40:43,120 --> 00:40:45,040
He looked into my eyes...

443
00:40:46,680 --> 00:40:49,240
with his piercing eyes.

444
00:40:51,240 --> 00:40:55,060
Like that we had our eyes locked for a long time.

445
00:40:56,010 --> 00:40:58,280
I really liked that,

446
00:40:59,440 --> 00:41:03,460
even though he passed away the next day.

447
00:41:05,320 --> 00:41:08,840
Yeah, I remember.

448
00:41:08,840 --> 00:41:12,350
You cried silently for such a long time.

449
00:41:13,340 --> 00:41:14,720
You remember?

450
00:41:14,720 --> 00:41:16,570
Of course.

451
00:41:17,740 --> 00:41:19,400
Yeah.

452
00:41:20,520 --> 00:41:24,220
You were there for that too.

453
00:41:24,220 --> 00:41:26,800
They are our histories of loyalty.

454
00:41:28,340 --> 00:41:30,190
That's right.

455
00:41:32,430 --> 00:41:36,940
Should I take a hit for paying for your loyalty?

456
00:41:36,940 --> 00:41:38,820
Are you serious?

457
00:41:38,820 --> 00:41:40,220
Yeah.

458
00:41:41,500 --> 00:41:45,000
Okay. Get ready!

459
00:41:45,000 --> 00:41:46,920
Where are you going to hit?

460
00:41:47,800 --> 00:41:51,480
Hey. It's no fun if I tell you that beforehand.

461
00:41:53,440 --> 00:41:55,210
- Oh...
- You—

462
00:41:55,210 --> 00:41:57,870
No, not my neck.

463
00:41:57,870 --> 00:42:01,320
I can't let you go near my face.

464
00:42:01,320 --> 00:42:03,800
Hey, Choi Won!

465
00:42:03,800 --> 00:42:08,040
Wow, that really hurt! Were you actually planning on hitting me?

466
00:42:08,040 --> 00:42:09,760
Of course!

467
00:42:09,760 --> 00:42:13,080
- "Of course"?!
- Of course!

468
00:42:13,080 --> 00:42:17,120
Wow, Oh Ha Na. You really have no limits.

469
00:42:19,380 --> 00:42:22,160
Cheapo.

470
00:42:22,160 --> 00:42:24,680
How could you have thought of hitting my face...

471
00:42:36,760 --> 00:42:38,390
Thank you.

472
00:42:40,890 --> 00:42:44,690
Won, I have something to confess...

473
00:42:44,690 --> 00:42:46,970
What is it? Did you lie about something or something?

474
00:42:46,970 --> 00:42:53,480
Earlier today, I met with Ha Na and Seo Hoo and Seo Hoo's teacher...

475
00:42:58,160 --> 00:42:59,960
Really?

476
00:42:59,960 --> 00:43:04,150
It sounds like it's going well for them. And for you too.

477
00:43:04,150 --> 00:43:06,910
Human emotions are a weird thing, huh.

478
00:43:06,910 --> 00:43:12,640
At first, when I learned that he was Seo Hoo's teacher, I thought, "No way."

479
00:43:12,640 --> 00:43:17,520
But I wanted to see him, so I just thought to myself, "So what if I go see him," and I went.

480
00:43:17,520 --> 00:43:21,860
I found that I kept looking for excuses to go see him...

481
00:43:21,860 --> 00:43:24,150
Just get rid of Cha Seo Hoo's name from your mind.

482
00:43:24,150 --> 00:43:27,020
and just do what you want. As long as you're happy, then it's fine.

483
00:43:27,020 --> 00:43:29,380
Won...

484
00:43:29,380 --> 00:43:34,960
And come introduce us sometime! It must be hard work, being with you. We should hang out.

485
00:43:36,320 --> 00:43:38,620
Thanks.

486
00:44:25,180 --> 00:44:27,420
To a friend who dodged my punch.

487
00:44:27,420 --> 00:44:29,830
Don't get sick and be healthy.

488
00:44:29,830 --> 00:44:32,880
What is this, Oh Ha Na?

489
00:44:51,550 --> 00:44:53,450
Welcome!

490
00:44:54,900 --> 00:44:57,070
Dae Bok!

491
00:45:02,270 --> 00:45:04,060
Aren't you tired?

492
00:45:04,060 --> 00:45:08,900
Ah, it's only my first day. I need to get my head back anyway.

493
00:45:10,030 --> 00:45:16,390
But Dae Bok, do we really have to keep the fact that we're meeting a secret?

494
00:45:16,390 --> 00:45:20,920
Mm. Think about it. My sister is the Team Leader, and you are her assistant.

495
00:45:20,920 --> 00:45:25,230
If your people find out you are meeting me, they'll say you used connections or your background.

496
00:45:25,230 --> 00:45:27,160
You'll just be misunderstood.

497
00:45:27,160 --> 00:45:29,970
Ah, okay. I get it.

498
00:45:29,970 --> 00:45:35,850
Just wait for a little bit. Once I've built myself up enough, I will proudly say,"This girl is my girl."

499
00:45:35,850 --> 00:45:40,450
I am not a material girl. I don't need presents.

500
00:45:40,450 --> 00:45:42,460
We don't even have to have dates in nice places.

501
00:45:42,460 --> 00:45:45,170
We have a lot of free coupons, right?

502
00:45:56,880 --> 00:45:59,280
Do you want to eat kimbap? I can get ramen too.

503
00:45:59,280 --> 00:46:00,940
Okay - sounds good!

504
00:46:01,700 --> 00:46:06,390
Dae Bok. Oh Dae Bok.

505
00:46:06,390 --> 00:46:09,750
From now on, I won't call you anything else.

506
00:46:21,730 --> 00:46:28,740
